data.name: Dark Porygon2

abilities.name: Spatial Distortion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose a Stadium card from your discard pile and put it into play. (If there's already a Stadium card in play, discard it.) This power can't be used if Dark Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Curve Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done by attacks to Dark Porygon2 during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

data.flavorText: Advances in technology have allowed it to evolve. It occasionally displays behavior not found in its programming.

abilities.name: 3-D Reset
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), return a Pokémon Tool card attached to 1 of your Pokémon to your hand. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Data Retrieval
attacks.text: If you have less than 8 cards in your hand, draw cards until you have 8 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Scramble Trip
attacks.text: If Porygon2 has a Scramble Energy card attached to it, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

data.name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Energy Converter
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon and choose an Energy type. Treat that Energy card as that type until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Porygon2 becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed, the Energy card goes back to its original type.

attacks.name: Delta Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose whether the Defending Pokémon becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: This upgraded version of Porygon is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

abilities.name: Backup
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have less than 6 cards in your hand, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Machine Burst
attacks.text: If Porygon2 has a Technical Machine card attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Burned.

data.name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Shortcut
abilities.text: The Retreat Cost for each Porygon, Porygon2, and Porygon-Z you have in play is Colorless less.

data.flavorText: This upgraded version of Porygon is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

data.name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Mapping
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Porygon2 from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for a Stadium card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: 3-D Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

data.flavorText: Further research enhanced its abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.

abilities.name: Backup
abilities.text: Once during each of your turns (before your attack), if you have 2 or fewer cards in your hand, you may draw cards from your deck until you have 3 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hypnotic Ray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Download
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Supporter card from your hand and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is affected by a Special Condition.

data.flavorText: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Tri Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

data.flavorText: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Destructive Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Calculate
attacks.text: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

data.flavorText: For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.

data.name: Porygon2
data.flavorText: AI has been installed in it. It learns various things all on its own, but it even remembers things it doesn't need to know.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Tri Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: Even though it doesn't die in the vacuum of space, it can't move around very well in zero gravity.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Garbage Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon Tool card in the Lost Zone (both yours and your opponent's).

data.flavorText: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

data.name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Powered Ball
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the Pokémon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

attacks.name: R Command
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name in your discard pile.

data.flavorText: This artificial Pokémon evolved thanks to cutting- edge science. It sometimes displays behavior that is not in its programming.
